WEBVTT

00:05.918 --> 00:07.050
PREVIOUSLY ON
"PUSHING DAISIES"...

00:07.094 --> 00:08.312
YOU ONLY GOT A MINUTE.
I KNOW.

00:08.356 --> 00:09.922
60 SECONDS.
I KNOW.

00:09.966 --> 00:10.967
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

00:11.011 --> 00:12.055
OHH!

00:12.838 --> 00:15.450
WHAT IF YOU
DIDN'T HAVE TO BE DEAD?

00:15.493 --> 00:17.843
Chuck: YOU TOUCH MURDER VICTIMS,
YOU ASK WHO KILLED THEM,

00:17.887 --> 00:19.802
YOU TOUCH THEM AGAIN,
THEY GO BACK TO BEING DEAD,

00:19.845 --> 00:21.151
AND YOU COLLECT
THE REWARD?

00:21.195 --> 00:22.892
THAT'S IT IN A NUTSHELL.

00:22.935 --> 00:24.807
Chuck: WE HAVEN'T SEEN
EACH OTHER IN, LIKE, 20 YEARS.

00:24.850 --> 00:26.374
DON'T YOU WANT TO KNOW
ABOUT ME? I WANT TO KNOW
EVERYTHING ABOUT YOU.

00:26.417 --> 00:29.072
Ned: LOOK, WE'VE ALL DONE
THINGS WE'RE NOT PROUD OF.

00:29.116 --> 00:30.378
WE ALL HAVE SECRETS.

00:30.421 --> 00:32.728
WHO'S THE FUNNY GIRL
STUCK TO NED?

00:32.771 --> 00:34.338
CHILDHOOD SWEETHEART.

00:34.382 --> 00:36.210
HE DIGS HER IN A WAY
HE DEFINITELY DOESN'T DIG YOU.

00:36.253 --> 00:38.908
I DON'T LIKE THAT GIRL,
NOT ONE BIT.

00:38.951 --> 00:40.910
WE RECENTLY LOST
OUR NIECE.

00:40.953 --> 00:42.477
YOUR NIECE,
CHARLOTTE CHARLES, IS DEAD?

00:42.520 --> 00:44.087
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

00:44.131 --> 00:46.394
OLIVE, WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING HERE?

00:46.437 --> 00:48.048
PIE DELIVERY.
TART APPLE.

00:56.447 --> 01:00.103
Narrator: THE SEASON WAS AUTUMN,
HIS FIRST YEAR AWAY.

01:00.147 --> 01:02.323
YOUNG NED
IS AT BOARDING SCHOOL.

01:02.366 --> 01:05.108
THE TIMES ARE NOT GAY.

01:05.152 --> 01:09.547
TUCKED AWAY IN HER LAIR,
DARK, DANK, AND COOL,

01:09.591 --> 01:13.508
STOOD THE POSTMISTRESS
OF THE LONGBOROUGH SCHOOL.

01:13.551 --> 01:16.815
EVERY WEEK, YOUNG NED
WOULD HOPE FOR A LETTER,

01:16.859 --> 01:19.514
SOME CONTACT FROM HOME
TO MAKE IT ALL BETTER.

01:19.557 --> 01:23.257
BUT FROM HIS FATHER,
THERE WAS NEVER A WORD.

01:23.300 --> 01:26.434
"HE'S GRIEVING YOUR MOTHER,"
THEY SAID.

01:26.477 --> 01:29.045
YOUNG NED WOULD CONCUR.

01:29.089 --> 01:31.874
THEN ONE DAY
BEFORE ALL HALLOWS' EVE,

01:31.917 --> 01:34.311
SHE GAVE HIM THE NOD.

01:34.355 --> 01:35.791
IT WAS HARD TO BELIEVE.

01:35.834 --> 01:38.272
HE WAS STUNNED TO BE SUMMONED,

01:38.315 --> 01:40.012
GUESSED WHAT HE'D BEEN GIVEN --

01:40.056 --> 01:44.495
CANDY CORN TREATS?
OR MASKS OF DEAD RISEN?

01:44.539 --> 01:48.064
BUT THE THING WAS MORE
FRIGHTENING THAN A DEMON,

01:48.108 --> 01:49.544
WINGED OR HOOVED --

01:49.587 --> 01:52.286
A PREPRINTED CARD
FROM HIS FATHER.

01:52.329 --> 01:53.852
"WE'VE MOVED."

01:59.423 --> 02:02.948
NED RAN AWAY.
NO ONE FROM SCHOOL SAW HIM GO.

02:02.992 --> 02:06.474
HE NEEDED TO SEE
WHAT THE POSTCARD WOULD SHOW.

02:06.517 --> 02:09.564
HIS FATHER'S NEW ADDRESS
WAS THE PLACE THAT HE SOUGHT,

02:09.607 --> 02:12.044
A HOME TO COME HOME TO.

02:12.088 --> 02:15.047
IN HIS THROAT,
HIS HEART CAUGHT.

02:15.091 --> 02:18.486
BUT WHAT CAME OUT OF THE DOOR
SCARED HIM FOR LIFE.

02:18.529 --> 02:21.053
HIS FATHER
WITH TWO BRAND-NEW SONS

02:21.097 --> 02:22.577
AND A BRAND-NEW WIFE.

02:22.620 --> 02:25.841
A HUG WAS WHAT HE WANTED,

02:25.884 --> 02:29.018
A WINK, AND A QUICK
"THE JOKE'S ON YOU."

02:29.061 --> 02:32.369
BUT WHAT HE GOT INSTEAD
WAS A HONEYCOMB CHEW.

02:32.413 --> 02:33.892
HAPPY HALLOWEEN.

02:39.898 --> 02:43.250
Narrator: NOW 20 YEARS LATER,
NEARLY TO THE HOUR,

02:43.293 --> 02:45.948
SOMEONE ELSE
WAS FEELING MELANCHOLY,

02:45.991 --> 02:48.603
AND SO VERY DOUR.

02:48.646 --> 02:50.692
[ RUMBLING ]

02:50.735 --> 02:54.478
THIS IS
WHERE THE GHOSTS RISE UP,

02:54.522 --> 02:56.785
ALLOWED TO WALK THE GROUND.

02:56.828 --> 02:58.003
[ HOWLING ]

03:00.963 --> 03:03.748
AND IF YOU'RE HAUNTED
BY YOUR PAST,

03:03.792 --> 03:06.098
YOU BEST NOT STICK AROUND.

03:06.142 --> 03:07.883
HELLO?

03:18.285 --> 03:20.112
[ NEIGHING ]

03:24.334 --> 03:25.205
AAH!

03:26.771 --> 03:28.643
Olive: NED HATES HALLOWEEN,
YOU KNOW.

03:28.686 --> 03:31.385
MAKES HIM MOODIER
THAN A PUMPKIN FULL OF PMS.

03:31.428 --> 03:33.430
Chuck: WHAT? NED DOESN'T
HATE HALLOWEEN.

03:33.474 --> 03:36.259
I'M PRETTY SURE TOMORROW'S
HIS LEAST-FAVORITE DAY.

03:36.303 --> 03:38.130
IN FACT,
WHEN HE SEES ALL THIS,

03:38.174 --> 03:39.828
YOU'RE GONNA BE
ONE SORRY LITTLE ZOMBIE.

03:39.871 --> 03:42.613
SERIOUSLY,
YOU ARE SO...DEAD.

03:46.487 --> 03:51.796
SO, UM, I GUESS YOU DELIVERED
SOME PIES TO MY AUNTS.

03:51.840 --> 03:53.189
YEAH, THEY'RE SWEET.

03:53.233 --> 03:54.799
PROBABLY BE A LOT SWEETER

03:54.843 --> 03:57.498
IF THEY DIDN'T THINK
YOU WERE...MURDERED.

03:57.541 --> 03:59.195
DID YOU TELL THEM
I WAS ALIVE?

03:59.239 --> 04:02.677
MM, KINDA THINK THAT MIGHT MAKE
THEIR LITTLE HEADS EXPLODE.

04:02.720 --> 04:03.939
WHAT WAS THAT RHYME?

04:03.982 --> 04:05.462
♪ I SCREAM, YOU SCREAM

04:05.506 --> 04:07.072
♪ WE ALL SCREAM
'CAUSE YOU FAKED YOUR DEATH ♪

04:07.116 --> 04:08.900
YOU THINK
I FAKED MY DEATH?

04:08.944 --> 04:10.250
THAT'S WHAT I JUST SANG.

04:10.293 --> 04:12.295
UNLESS YOU HAVE
A BETTER EXPLANATION.

04:12.339 --> 04:15.951
Narrator: THE FACT THAT
THE TRUTH WAS TOO UNIMAGINABLE

04:15.994 --> 04:18.519
EVEN TO BE CONSIDERED
RELIEVED CHUCK.

04:18.562 --> 04:20.434
BUT THERE WERE OTHER PROBLEMS.

04:21.522 --> 04:23.959
OLIVE. CHUCK.

04:28.311 --> 04:30.052
SPOOKY.

04:31.271 --> 04:33.664
WE DON'T USUALLY DECORATE
FOR HALLOWEEN...

04:33.708 --> 04:35.231
THIS MUCH.

04:35.275 --> 04:36.493
OR AT ALL.

04:36.537 --> 04:38.147
YEAH, I'LL HAVE THEM DOWN
IN A JIFFY.

04:38.190 --> 04:39.844
CHUCK JUST HAD HER HEAD
UP HER --

04:39.888 --> 04:42.107
NO, IT'S OKAY.
LEAVE THEM UP.

04:42.151 --> 04:44.022
PROBABLY GOOD FOR BUSINESS.

04:44.066 --> 04:45.589
I MEAN...

04:45.633 --> 04:47.809
THANKS, CHUCK.

04:51.421 --> 04:54.685
NED USED TO LOVE
HALLOWEEN.

04:54.729 --> 04:56.992
YEAH. I GUESS I KNOW NED
BETTER THAN YOU DO.

04:57.035 --> 04:59.081
AND NOW I KNOW YOU
BETTER THAN NED DOES.

04:59.124 --> 05:01.518
SO, DOES NED KNOW WHAT
YOU THINK YOU KNOW?
NOT YET.

05:01.562 --> 05:04.478
WHO DOES?
WHO KNOWS?

05:06.393 --> 05:09.700
Narrator:
OLIVE SNOOK LOVED TO WIN.

05:09.744 --> 05:12.703
SHE CELEBRATED THE FACT
THAT THE UNFLAPPABLE BRUNETTE

05:12.747 --> 05:16.054
WHO HAD SWEPT IN FROM NOWHERE
TO STEAL THE PIE MAKER'S HEART,

05:16.098 --> 05:19.449
MIGHT BE FLAPPABLE AFTER ALL.

05:19.493 --> 05:23.061
BUT, AS OFTEN HAPPENS
WHEN ONE CELEBRATES,

05:23.105 --> 05:26.717
THE UNIVERSE IS QUICK
TO EVEN THE SCORE.

05:26.761 --> 05:30.068
Reporter:
A SAD ENDING FOR LOCAL
BLACKSMITH LUCAS SHOEMAKER...

05:30.112 --> 05:31.679
JIMINY CHRISTMAS!

05:31.722 --> 05:33.333
...WHO WAS TRAMPLED TO DEATH
LATE YESTERDAY

05:33.376 --> 05:35.073
WHILE WORKING
AT MANCHESTER DOWNS.

05:35.117 --> 05:37.554
POLICE HAVE AGREED
THAT THE DEATH WAS UNUSUAL,

05:37.598 --> 05:40.035
CONSIDERING THE VICTIM'S
EXPERIENCE WITH HORSES,

05:40.078 --> 05:43.125
BUT THEY SAY THEY DO NOT
SUSPECT ANY FOUL PLAY

05:43.168 --> 05:44.431
AT THIS TIME.

05:44.474 --> 05:46.911
IN OTHER NEWS, KITTENS ON --

05:46.955 --> 05:49.392
[ TELEVISION TURNS OFF ]

05:50.959 --> 05:54.397
I KNOW THE DECORATIONS
WERE A LOT OF WORK.

05:54.441 --> 05:56.791
THIS HAS ALWAYSBEEN
MY FAVORITE HOLIDAY.

05:56.834 --> 05:59.402
REMEMBER WHEN WE USED TO GO
TRICK-OR-TREATING,

05:59.446 --> 06:00.925
GORGE OURSELVES ON CANDY?

06:02.753 --> 06:04.102
YOU USED TO LOVE THAT.

06:06.017 --> 06:07.976
WHY DON'T YOU LIKE
HALLOWEEN ANYMORE?

06:08.019 --> 06:10.457
REMEMBER RAZOR BLADES
IN APPLES?

06:10.500 --> 06:13.416
NEVER ACTUALLY HAPPENED,
UH, NOT ONCE.

06:13.460 --> 06:14.896
JUST VICIOUS RUMOR.

06:14.939 --> 06:17.159
ARE YOU CHANGING
THE SUBJECT?
NO.

06:17.202 --> 06:18.334
HAVE YOU SEEN OLIVE?

06:18.378 --> 06:19.466
OLIVE?

06:19.509 --> 06:21.163
I WONDER WHERE SHE WENT.

06:21.206 --> 06:24.427
Narrator: CHUCK IMAGINED
WHERE OLIVE MIGHT BE.

06:24.471 --> 06:26.647
LADIES, I LOVE YOUR TEA,
AND YOUR HOUSE IS SO CUTE.

06:26.690 --> 06:28.213
OH, BY THE WAY,
CHUCK'S ALIVE.

06:30.738 --> 06:32.348
WHAT'S WRONG?
NOTHING.

06:32.392 --> 06:35.525
I SAID "OLIVE" AND YOUR
WHOLE FACE JUST WENT WHOOSH.

06:35.569 --> 06:37.701
WHY DON'T YOU LIKE
HALLOWEEN ANYMORE?

06:37.745 --> 06:39.573
THINGS CHANGE.
I GREW UP.

06:39.616 --> 06:41.270
YOU GREW UP?

06:41.313 --> 06:43.359
ARE YOUCHANGING THE SUBJECT?
WHY THE WHOOSH?

06:43.403 --> 06:45.492
THAT'S HOW I LOOK NOW
WHEN I FEEL NOTHING.

06:45.535 --> 06:48.016
MY FACE RELAXES INTO SOMETHING
THAT LOOKS NERVOUS.

06:48.059 --> 06:50.235
DIDN'T USED TO.

06:50.279 --> 06:52.803
THINGS CHANGE.
I GREW UP.

06:56.067 --> 06:59.375
Narrator: AS THE PIE MAKER
WALKED OUT ONE DOOR,

06:59.419 --> 07:01.464
OLIVE OPENED ANOTHER.

07:01.508 --> 07:03.466
[ GRUNTS ]

07:03.510 --> 07:07.035
Narrator: AS SHE LOOKED IN,
A SECRET FLOODED OVER HER

07:07.078 --> 07:10.691
AS SHARP AND HORRIBLE
AS THE DAY SHE HAD SEALED IT IN.

07:10.734 --> 07:12.301
CHECK, PLEASE.

07:13.084 --> 07:15.043
OR CASH.
CASH IS GOOD.

07:15.086 --> 07:16.610
I WANT TO HIRE YOU.

07:16.653 --> 07:17.915
TECHNICALLY,
I ALREADY HAVE,

07:17.959 --> 07:19.526
SINCE YOU WERE SO GRABBY
WITH THE CASH.

07:19.569 --> 07:21.876
THINK OF IT AS IN ESCROW
BETWEEN MY THIGHS.

07:21.919 --> 07:23.355
WHAT'S THE CASE?

07:23.399 --> 07:26.141
YESTERDAY, A FARRIER
NAMED LUCAS SHOEMAKER

07:26.184 --> 07:27.925
WAS FOUND DEAD, TRAMPLED.

07:27.969 --> 07:30.624
WHY SHOULD I CARE ABOUT
A DUDE THAT SELLS FUR COATS?

07:30.667 --> 07:32.234
NOT A FURRIER.
A FARRIER.

07:32.277 --> 07:33.235
"AIR."

07:33.278 --> 07:34.628
FARRIER?

07:34.671 --> 07:36.456
IT'S A BLACKSMITH.
PUTS SHOES ON HORSES.

07:36.499 --> 07:39.459
DON'T TRY TO ACT LIKE
THAT'S A WORD EVERYBODY KNOWS.

07:39.502 --> 07:41.461
POLICE ARE SAYING
HIS DEATH WAS AN...

07:42.766 --> 07:44.420
...ACCIDENT.

07:44.464 --> 07:47.423
YOU GOT REASON
TO THINK OTHERWISE?
I MIGHT.

07:47.467 --> 07:49.425
THIS FARRIER,
A FRIEND OF YOURS?WE USED TO WORK TOGETHER.

07:49.469 --> 07:51.906
HE EVER PUT SHOES
ON OR OFF OF YOU?WASN'T LIKE THAT.

07:51.949 --> 07:53.560
WE WERE...

07:53.603 --> 07:55.083
COMPETITORS.

07:55.126 --> 07:56.171
WHAT DID YOU COMPETE ABOUT?

07:56.214 --> 07:57.781
PROMISE YOU WON'T LAUGH?

07:57.825 --> 07:58.956
NO.

08:00.784 --> 08:02.960
I USED TO BE
A PROFESSIONAL HORSE JOCKEY.

08:04.788 --> 08:06.616
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:06.660 --> 08:09.358
[ LAUGHING ]

08:09.401 --> 08:11.316
[ LAUGHING LOUDER ]

08:11.360 --> 08:12.622
Shut up!

08:14.145 --> 08:16.017
[ LAUGHING LOUDLY ]

08:16.974 --> 08:19.368
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

08:19.411 --> 08:21.805
FOR 8 YEARS,
11 WEEKS, AND 4 DAYS,

08:21.849 --> 08:24.155
OLIVE SNOOK HAD BEEN A JOCKEY.

08:24.199 --> 08:25.896
AT THE PEAK OF HER CAREER,

08:25.940 --> 08:28.943
SHE WAS CONSIDERED AMONG THE
BEST AND BRIGHTEST OF HER SPORT.

08:28.986 --> 08:31.598
LUCAS SHOEMAKER HAD ALSO BEEN
A FREQUENT VISITOR

08:31.641 --> 08:33.425
TO THE WINNER'S CIRCLE.

08:33.469 --> 08:35.515
THEN, UPON REACHING THE AGE

08:35.558 --> 08:39.040
OF 45 YEARS, 3 WEEKS,
4 DAYS, AND 4 HOURS OLD,

08:39.083 --> 08:42.652
HE RETIRED FOR A SECOND TIME...
PERMANENTLY.

08:46.090 --> 08:48.919
IS THIS A BAD IDEA,
OLIVE AS A CLIENT?

08:48.963 --> 08:50.355
IT'S A LITTLE TOO CLOSE
FOR COMFORT.

08:50.399 --> 08:52.967
OH, HANG ON A SECOND.
LET ME ASK THE MONEY.

08:53.010 --> 08:55.230
HEY, MONEY, IT'S ME, EMERSON.

08:55.273 --> 08:57.972
I'M GOOD. I'M GOOD.
YEAH, THANKS FOR ASKING.

08:58.015 --> 09:00.322
SAY, CAN I STILL PAY MY BILLS
AND BUY STUFF WITH YOU,

09:00.365 --> 09:02.193
EVEN THOUGH YOU WAS
OLIVE'S MONEY FIRST?

09:02.237 --> 09:03.194
UH-HUH.

09:04.369 --> 09:05.545
YEAH.

09:05.588 --> 09:08.069
[ Chuckling ]
OKAY, THEN. THANKS.

09:08.112 --> 09:10.201
THE MONEY DON'T CARE.
TOUCH HIM.

09:15.946 --> 09:16.991
HI.

09:17.034 --> 09:18.383
HI. UGH.

09:19.733 --> 09:21.082
UGH.

09:21.125 --> 09:23.040
THIS MAY SEEM LIKE
ASKING THE OBVIOUS,

09:23.084 --> 09:25.390
BUT WERE YOU TRAMPLED
BY A HORSE?

09:25.434 --> 09:28.829
YEAH.
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

09:28.872 --> 09:30.918
THEY PUT A BOMB
IN YOUR DAYBED?

09:30.961 --> 09:33.181
NO.
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

09:33.224 --> 09:35.139
JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS
KILLED YOU?
YEAH.

09:35.183 --> 09:36.880
HOW CAN YOU
UNDERSTAND HIM?

09:36.924 --> 09:39.840
I WAS IN FULL ORTHODONTIC
HEADGEAR FOR THREE YEARS.

09:39.883 --> 09:41.450
WHEN?
PUBERTY.

09:41.493 --> 09:42.930
YOU ALWAYS
HAD NICE TEETH.

09:42.973 --> 09:44.540
MY AUNTS TOLD ME IT WAS
A FORM OF BIRTH CONTROL.

09:44.584 --> 09:46.542
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]YES, IT DID SUCK.

09:46.586 --> 09:48.196
CAN WE GET ON
WITH THIS, PLEASE?

09:48.239 --> 09:50.851
SO, YOU'RE SURE
JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS KILLED YOU?

09:50.894 --> 09:52.548
[ Mumbling ]
YEAH.

09:52.592 --> 09:54.681
I ASSURE YOU, MR. SHOEMAKER,
JUSTICE WILL BE SERVED.

09:54.724 --> 09:56.073
[ Mumbling ]
WAIT. EXCEPT...

09:56.117 --> 09:58.032
HERE IT IS.
EXCEPT WHAT?

09:58.075 --> 09:59.163
HE'S DEAD.

10:00.687 --> 10:02.079
W-WHO'S DEAD?

10:02.123 --> 10:04.429
[ SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

10:04.473 --> 10:07.911
JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS DIED
SEVEN YEARS AGO. HE SAW IT.

10:09.173 --> 10:10.740
HIS GOPE KILL ME.

10:10.784 --> 10:12.220
HIS GOAT KILLED YOU?

10:12.263 --> 10:14.439
GOPE.

10:15.484 --> 10:16.659
GOPE.

10:16.703 --> 10:19.096
[ High-pitched voice ]
OOOOOOOH!

10:20.271 --> 10:22.186
AND HE'S GOING TO
KIM AGEM.

10:24.275 --> 10:25.755
THAT SOUNDED LIKE...

10:25.799 --> 10:27.801
A GHOST.
A GHOST KILLED HIM.

10:27.844 --> 10:30.107
AND HE'S GOING TO KILL
"AGEM."

10:34.677 --> 10:36.679
MOST PEOPLE HEAR "GHOST,"

10:36.723 --> 10:38.812
AND THEY THINK OF
A DISEMBODIED DEAD
SEA CAPTAIN OR SOMETHING.

10:38.855 --> 10:41.118
BUT THERE'S ACTUALLY
AN ENTIRE SPECTRUM OF GHOSTS.

10:41.162 --> 10:42.772
I'M FINE
WITH DEAD SEA CAPTAIN.

10:42.816 --> 10:44.339
YOU DON'T REALLY BELIEVE

10:44.382 --> 10:46.950
A GHOST KILLED
LUCAS SHOEMAKER, DO YOU?

10:46.994 --> 10:48.778
I'LL BET SHE DOES.

10:48.822 --> 10:50.824
HOW DO YOU KNOW THERE'S NOT
A GHOST SOMEWHERE RIGHT NOW

10:50.867 --> 10:52.129
TELLING HIS GHOST FRIEND,

10:52.173 --> 10:53.696
"YOU DON'T REALLY THINK
THERE'S A GUY

10:53.740 --> 10:54.654
WHO CAN TOUCH DEAD PEOPLE
BACK TO LIFE, DO YOU?"

10:54.697 --> 10:56.003
THAT'S NOT FAIR.

10:56.046 --> 10:57.526
JUST BECAUSE THERE'S MAGIC
IN ONEPLACE

10:57.569 --> 10:58.962
DOESN'T MEAN THERE'S MAGIC
IN EVERYPLACE.

10:59.006 --> 11:01.008
I DON'T BELIEVE IN GHOSTS
OR WITCHES

11:01.051 --> 11:02.792
OR HAUNTED HOUSES
OR SPIRITS.

11:02.836 --> 11:04.576
AND MAYBE THAT SOUNDS
A LITTLE CRAZY

11:04.620 --> 11:07.318
COMING FROM A GUY WHO CAN
SHOOT SPARKS OUT OF HIS FINGER,

11:07.362 --> 11:08.668
BUT THAT'S WHAT I BELIEVE.

11:08.711 --> 11:10.321
YOU USED TO
BELIEVE IN GHOSTS.

11:10.365 --> 11:12.802
HE USED TO THINK
MY AUNTS' HOUSE WAS HAUNTED.

11:12.846 --> 11:15.631
WE HAD A SéANCE THERE
ONE NIGHT.

11:15.675 --> 11:17.241
He peed his pants.

11:17.285 --> 11:19.156
[ Chuckling ]
I DID NOT.

11:19.200 --> 11:21.028
[ LAUGHS ]

11:23.378 --> 11:25.685
I KNOCKED THE HORS D'OEUVRE
PLATE INTO MY LAP,

11:25.728 --> 11:27.121
AND THE BRIE WAS RUNNY.

11:27.164 --> 11:29.689
I'D STICK WITH
THE PISSING-MY-PANTS STORY.

11:30.820 --> 11:33.301
OH, THERE'S OLIVE.

11:38.741 --> 11:41.701
YOU WERE RIGHT.
LUCAS SHOEMAKER WAS MURDERED.

11:41.744 --> 11:44.007
I KNEW IT.
WORD IS
THERE COULD BE MORE.

11:44.051 --> 11:45.922
KNOW WHO ELSE
MIGHT BE IN DANGER?

11:45.966 --> 11:47.054
MIGHT BE JOCKEYS.

11:47.097 --> 11:48.838
YOU GOT NAMES?
GOT PLACES.

11:48.882 --> 11:50.927
BAR I KNOW.
BUNCH OF THEM HANG OUT.

11:50.971 --> 11:54.104
THE NAME JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS
MEAN ANYTHING TO YOU?

11:54.148 --> 11:56.411
W-W-W-WHY?

11:56.454 --> 11:59.631
SOMEONE SAID
THEY SAW HIS GHOST.

11:59.675 --> 12:02.112
OH. UH...

12:05.986 --> 12:09.119
Narrator: IT WAS PLAIN
THAT THE NAME JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS

12:09.163 --> 12:12.209
MEANT EVERYTHING
TO OLIVE SNOOK.

12:12.253 --> 12:14.037
THAT NAME
MEANS EVERYTHING TO HER.

12:14.081 --> 12:15.473
I'M GONNA CHECK OUT

12:15.517 --> 12:17.780
WHO ELSE KNOWS ABOUT
THIS SUPPOSED GHOST.

12:17.824 --> 12:19.216
OLIVE SAID THERE WAS A BAR.

12:19.260 --> 12:20.522
I'LL CHECK OUT THE STABLES,

12:20.565 --> 12:21.958
SEE IF THE PERP
LEFT BEHIND ANY CLUES.

12:22.002 --> 12:24.613
YOU MEAN LIKE PROTOPLASM
OR MELTED CRUCIFIXES?

12:24.656 --> 12:26.136
OR, YOU KNOW, REAL CLUES.

12:26.180 --> 12:27.398
DID HE SAY "PERP"?

12:27.442 --> 12:29.487
HE DID.
ISN'T HE CUTE?

12:29.531 --> 12:30.619
HMM.

12:30.662 --> 12:33.274
I'LL COME WITH YOU
IF YOU LIKE.

12:33.317 --> 12:35.624
ACTUALLY,
I'D RATHER GO ALONE.

12:35.667 --> 12:38.235
BESIDES,
I THINK EMERSON NEEDS YOU.

12:38.279 --> 12:39.497
WHAT?

12:39.541 --> 12:40.542
OW!

12:40.585 --> 12:41.891
DON'T KICK ME.

12:41.935 --> 12:44.285
DID YOU JUST KICK HIM
UNDER THE TABLE?

12:44.328 --> 12:45.808
NO.

12:45.852 --> 12:47.114
[ GASPS ]
YES.

12:47.157 --> 12:49.812
THERE'S JUST SOMETHING ELSE
I GOT TO DO.

12:49.856 --> 12:52.206
CASE RELATED?
YES.

12:53.120 --> 12:54.643
NO.

12:54.686 --> 12:58.778
IN FACT, I PROBABLY WON'T EVEN
MAKE IT TO THE STABLES.

12:58.821 --> 13:01.650
FINE. I'LL GO TO THE STABLES.
YOU GO TO THE BAR.

13:01.693 --> 13:03.957
YOU GO AND DO WHATEVER
PRIVATE, SECRET, ALONE THING

13:04.000 --> 13:05.610
YOU NEED TO GO AND DO
BY YOURSELF.

13:05.654 --> 13:07.787
ALONE.

13:13.836 --> 13:15.403
SHE'S UPSET.

13:15.446 --> 13:18.014
BUT THIS REALLYIS SOMETHING
I HAVE TO DO ALONE.

13:18.058 --> 13:20.147
TELLING ME HELPS.

13:21.801 --> 13:22.976
WHERE'S OLIVE?

13:23.019 --> 13:24.716
OH, SHOOT.

13:25.979 --> 13:29.156
Narrator: THE REASON
60% OF OLIVE SNOOK'S BLOOD

13:29.199 --> 13:31.767
HAD LEFT HER HEAD WAS THIS --

13:31.811 --> 13:35.031
FOR 3 YEARS,
4 MONTHS, AND 26 DAYS,

13:35.075 --> 13:39.253
JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS HAD BEEN
THE GOLDEN BOY OF HORSE RACING.

13:39.296 --> 13:41.603
WIN AFTER WIN
ON THE WORLD CIRCUIT

13:41.646 --> 13:44.649
EARNED HIM GRANDER TROPHIES
AND GREATER PURSES

13:44.693 --> 13:46.129
UNTIL HE WAS A SURE BET

13:46.173 --> 13:49.350
TO BECOME THE GREATEST JOCKEY
OF ALL TIME.

13:49.393 --> 13:52.614
HIS CHANCE TO PROVE THIS
CAME IN THE RACE OF THE CENTURY,

13:52.657 --> 13:55.704
PITTING THE TOP JOCKEYS
OF THE DAY AGAINST EACH OTHER.

13:55.747 --> 13:59.316
BUT AS HE WAS ABOUT TO WIN
THE JOCK-OFF 2000,

13:59.360 --> 14:04.495
JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS SUDDENLY
FOUND HIMSELF...UNSEATED.

14:04.539 --> 14:06.149
HIS PATENTED EARLY LEAD,

14:06.193 --> 14:08.804
IDEAL FOR WINNING
BUT NOT FOR FALLING,

14:08.848 --> 14:11.328
LED TO HIS BEING
UNWITTINGLY TRAMPLED

14:11.372 --> 14:14.201
BY THE FOUR OTHER RIDERS
IN THE RACE,

14:14.244 --> 14:18.509
INCLUDING THE JOCK-OFF 2000'S
EVENTUAL WINNER, OLIVE SNOOK.

14:18.553 --> 14:20.511
I QUIT RACING
THE NEXT DAY,

14:20.555 --> 14:23.297
PUT THE TROPHY AND MY WINNINGS
IN A SAFE-DEPOSIT BOX.

14:23.340 --> 14:25.212
I THOUGHT
IF I LOCKED IT ALL AWAY,

14:25.255 --> 14:27.257
I COULD...FORGET.

14:27.301 --> 14:28.998
YOU THINK WHOEVER
KILLED SHOEMAKER

14:29.042 --> 14:31.740
WAS LOOKING TO GET REVENGE
FOR JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS' DEATH?

14:31.783 --> 14:34.917
I KNOW IT SOUNDS CRAZY.IT AIN'T CRAZY.

14:34.961 --> 14:37.267
A GUY'S SUPPOSED TO WIN A RACE,
AND THEN HE DOESN'T.

14:37.311 --> 14:39.617
A LOT OF ANGRY GAMBLERS
LOOKING FOR SOMEONE TO BLAME.

14:39.661 --> 14:43.360
BUT WHY NOW? SEVEN YEARS IS
A LONG TIME TO NURSE A GRUDGE.

14:43.404 --> 14:44.884
WHAT IF IT IS
JOHN JOSEPH'S GHOST?

14:44.927 --> 14:46.015
WELL, SEE,
NOW, THAT'S CRAZY.

14:46.059 --> 14:47.451
WHAT IF HE'S
GOING AFTER EVERYBODY

14:47.495 --> 14:49.497
WHO FINISHED THE RACE
WHERE HE DIED?

14:49.540 --> 14:51.673
GORDON WAS FOURTH.
SHOE SHOWED THIRD.

14:51.716 --> 14:52.892
PINKY PLACED SECOND.

14:52.935 --> 14:55.590
I NEVER SHOULD HAVE WON.

14:55.633 --> 14:58.288
YOU NEED ANOTHER DRINK.

14:58.332 --> 15:00.290
BARKEEP!

15:00.334 --> 15:01.901
[ Irish accent ]
HEY, LISTEN, KING KONG.

15:01.944 --> 15:03.946
I ALREADY TOLD YOU.
YOU CAN FINISH YOUR BEER AND GO.

15:03.990 --> 15:05.817
WE DON'T WANT YOUR KIND
IN HERE.
HEY!

15:05.861 --> 15:08.385
TAKE A BREATH, BIG FELLA.

15:08.429 --> 15:11.388
I'M MERELY REFERRING TO
THE SIGN BEHIND THE BAR.

15:12.912 --> 15:15.784
DAMN IT, PINKY McCOY.
I'M TRYING TO SAVE YOUR LIFE.

15:15.827 --> 15:17.264
WILL YOU JUST CALM DOWN?

15:17.307 --> 15:18.613
THE P.I.'s HERE ABOUT SHOEY.

15:18.656 --> 15:20.441
HE JUST WANTS TO ASK YOU
SOME QUESTIONS.

15:22.095 --> 15:23.096
OH.

15:24.358 --> 15:25.794
WHY DO THEY CALL YOU
PINKY?

15:25.837 --> 15:28.144
IF YOU'RE LOOKING TO MAKE
A JOKE AT MY EXPENSE...

15:28.188 --> 15:29.929
IT'S JUST A QUESTION.

15:29.972 --> 15:32.453
KNOCK IT OFF, THE BOTH OF YOU!
AND YOU PUT THAT GUN AWAY!

15:32.496 --> 15:34.411
[ Slurring ]
LISTEN TO THE LITTLE LADY.

15:34.455 --> 15:37.762
A BIRD GUN LIKE THAT
AIN'T GONNA DO YOU NO GOOD

15:37.806 --> 15:40.504
IF THE GHOST
OF JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS

15:40.548 --> 15:42.289
COMES A-CALLING FOR YOU.

15:42.332 --> 15:44.160
SHUT YOUR TRAP, GORDON!

15:44.204 --> 15:46.293
YOU SEEN THIS GHOST,
FRIEND?

15:46.336 --> 15:48.512
OH, I'VE SEEN HIM,
ALL RIGHT.

15:48.556 --> 15:54.170
HE RISES FROM HIS GRAVE AND
WALKS THE STABLES BY NIGHT...

15:54.214 --> 15:55.432
OH, BROTHER.

15:55.476 --> 15:57.652
...LOOKING FOR REVENGE

15:57.695 --> 16:00.960
ON THE RIDERS
WHO MANGLED HIM.

16:02.309 --> 16:04.789
OH, NO.
THEN IT'S TRUE.

16:04.833 --> 16:08.880
THE GHOST OF JOHN JOSEPH
MURDERED THAT JOCKEY.

16:08.924 --> 16:11.796
AND HE'LL GET
THE REST OF US, TOO,

16:11.840 --> 16:15.626
ONE BY BLOODY ONE.

16:15.670 --> 16:17.454
THAT'S IT!
I'M CUTTING YOU OFF!

16:17.498 --> 16:20.718
THE ONLY THING THAT GHOST'S
A-MURDERING IS MY BUSINESS.

16:20.762 --> 16:22.329
YOU DON'T BELIEVE ME,

16:22.372 --> 16:25.245
YOU GO LOOK AT HIS TOMB
FOR YOURSELF.

16:25.288 --> 16:27.812
THE LID'S BEEN BROKEN

16:27.856 --> 16:31.991
ON ACCOUNT OF HIM CLIMBING OUT
ALL THE TIME.

16:34.558 --> 16:36.560
Olive:
WHO EATS IN A TOMB?

16:36.604 --> 16:38.475
THERE'S CRACKERS EVERYWHERE.

16:38.519 --> 16:42.001
WHOEVER IT WAS COULDN'T HAVE
BEEN HERE VERY LONG AGO.

16:42.044 --> 16:43.306
GORDON WAS RIGHT.

16:43.350 --> 16:45.221
THE LID'S BEEN BROKEN,
JUST LIKE HE SAID.

16:45.265 --> 16:47.354
MAYBE JOHN JOSEPH IS
COMING BACK FROM THE DEAD.

16:47.397 --> 16:49.095
OR SOMEONE WANTS TO GIVE
THAT IMPRESSION.

16:49.138 --> 16:50.835
MAYBE GORDON KNOWS MORE
THAN HE'S LETTING ON.

16:50.879 --> 16:52.098
WE GOT TO LOOK INSIDE.

16:52.141 --> 16:53.664
MAYBE JOHN JOSEPH
FAKED HIS DEATH.

16:53.708 --> 16:54.926
PEOPLE DO THAT ALL THE TIME.

16:54.970 --> 16:55.884
NO, THEY DON'T.

16:55.927 --> 16:57.320
YEAH, THEY DO.

16:57.364 --> 16:59.844
SOMETIMES THEY JUST DON'T
EVEN TRY TO COVER IT UP.

16:59.888 --> 17:01.672
THEY JUST SHOW UP
AND RUIN YOUR LIFE

17:01.716 --> 17:03.283
LIKE NO ONE'S EVER GONNA
FIGURE IT OUT.

17:03.326 --> 17:05.502
BUT THEN YOU DO FIGURE IT OUT
'CAUSE YOU'RE NOT AN IDIOT.

17:05.546 --> 17:07.200
ARE YOU AN IDIOT?

17:07.243 --> 17:09.071
NO, BECAUSE AN IDIOT
MIGHT MISUNDERSTAND
WHAT YOU'RE SAYING

17:09.115 --> 17:10.333
AND HIT YOU
WITH A SHOVEL.

17:10.377 --> 17:12.553
I THINK YOU KNOW.

17:12.596 --> 17:14.772
I THINK YOU'RE WRONG.
CAN WE DO THIS?

17:14.816 --> 17:15.991
YEAH.

17:31.093 --> 17:32.442
OH, YOU WANT TO DO IT.

17:32.486 --> 17:33.748
OKAY. YEAH.

17:43.758 --> 17:45.716
1...

17:45.760 --> 17:48.632
2...

17:48.676 --> 17:50.069
[ Groaning ]
SHUT UP.

17:50.112 --> 17:51.418
...3!

17:53.811 --> 17:56.336
SWEET SECRETARIAT!

17:56.379 --> 17:58.773
OH, THAT DON'T LOOK LIKE
JOHN JOSEPH.

17:58.816 --> 18:00.557
A HORSE WITH NO NAME.

18:00.601 --> 18:01.906
OR LEGS.

18:01.950 --> 18:04.735
[ BOTH SHUDDERING ]

18:08.217 --> 18:10.089
HELLO?

18:10.132 --> 18:11.786
HELLO, IS ANYBODY HERE?

18:11.829 --> 18:12.961
[ NEIGHING ]

18:13.004 --> 18:14.789
NAY YOURSELF.

18:14.832 --> 18:16.269
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]

18:16.312 --> 18:18.488
COME ON, DIGBY,
LET'S GO LOOK FOR EVIDENCE.

18:18.532 --> 18:19.881
YOU KNOW,
IF YOU THINK ABOUT IT,

18:19.924 --> 18:21.317
WE'VE ALREADY
BEEN MURDERED ONCE.

18:21.361 --> 18:24.929
HOW MANY PEOPLE OR DOGS
CAN SAY THAT, HUH?

18:24.973 --> 18:26.714
YOU KNOW WHAT WE ARE?

18:26.757 --> 18:29.282
WE'RE THE WALKING DEAD
ON HALLOWEEN.

18:29.325 --> 18:32.415
IF ANYONE SHOULD BE SCARED,
IT SHOULD BE THEM.

18:36.680 --> 18:40.075
OH, LOOK, SOMEONE DROPPED
AN OYSTER --

18:40.119 --> 18:41.468
AAH!

18:41.511 --> 18:42.730
OH!

18:42.773 --> 18:44.123
EMERSON!

18:46.864 --> 18:48.649
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

18:48.692 --> 18:51.042
THERE'S A LEGLESS SKELETON OF
A HORSE IN JOHN JACOB'S TOMB,

18:51.086 --> 18:52.348
AND OLIVE KNOWS
YOU'RE DEAD.

18:52.392 --> 18:53.784
FIRST OF ALL, HUH?

18:53.828 --> 18:56.178
AND SECONDLY, OLIVE THINKS
THAT I FAKED MY DEATH,

18:56.222 --> 18:58.833
WHICH IS COMPLETELY DIFFERENT
TO KNOWING THAT I'M DEAD.

18:58.876 --> 19:00.617
YEAH, DIFFERENT
LIKE PURPLE AND MAUVE.

19:00.661 --> 19:02.184
I WAS SENDING PIES
TO MY AUNTS.

19:02.228 --> 19:04.578
I DIDN'T KNOW OLIVE
WAS GONNA DELIVER THEM.

19:04.621 --> 19:06.841
THIS IS EXACTLY
WHAT NED WAS AFRAID OF.

19:06.884 --> 19:09.191
NOW SHE CAN RUIN EVERYTHING.

19:09.235 --> 19:11.193
I HOPE HE'S OKAY,
WHEREVER HE IS.

19:11.237 --> 19:12.934
Narrator: AT THAT MOMENT,

19:12.977 --> 19:16.372
THE PIE MAKER FOUND HIMSELF
ACROSS TOWN AND ACROSS TIME.

19:17.765 --> 19:19.636
HAPPY HALLOWEEN.

19:21.551 --> 19:23.945
Narrator: DAD'S HEART HAD DONE
WHAT IT NEEDED THE MOST.

19:23.988 --> 19:27.035
IT MOVED ON
AND NEVER LOOKED BACK,

19:27.078 --> 19:30.908
TILL NED WAS NOTHING...
BUT A GHOST.

19:30.952 --> 19:34.999
SO, THE GHOST RAN AWAY,
ONE THOUGHT IN HIS HEAD --

19:35.043 --> 19:39.569
TO GO BACK TO HIS OLD HOUSE
AND LIE DOWN IN HIS BED.

19:39.613 --> 19:43.573
BUT YOU CAN'T GO BACK IN TIME,
ANY GHOST CAN SEE.

19:43.617 --> 19:46.794
SO, HE LAID DOWN
WHERE HIS BED USEDTO BE.

19:49.275 --> 19:53.104
20 YEARS WENT BY.
PAINT CHIPPED, GRASS GREW.

19:53.148 --> 19:57.239
YOUNG NED NEVER FORGOT,
AND YOUNG NED GREW, TOO.

19:57.283 --> 20:01.722
SO HE CAME BACK TO HAUNT THE
HOUSE WHERE GOOD TIMES WERE HAD

20:01.765 --> 20:04.464
TILL THE TIMES,
THEY'D MARCHED ON,

20:04.507 --> 20:06.422
AND WITH THEM, DAD.

20:06.466 --> 20:10.383
[ LAUGHTER ]

20:10.426 --> 20:12.863
Lily: HEY, KID,
THROW ANOTHER EGG,

20:12.907 --> 20:16.563
AND YOU HAVE MY WORD, IT'LL BE
THE LAST EGG YOU EVER THROW.

20:16.606 --> 20:20.262
THAT'S RIGHT.
RUN, YOU LITTLE BASTARDS.

20:23.831 --> 20:25.180
WELL, WHOEVER KILLED
SHOEMAKER

20:25.224 --> 20:27.095
OBVIOUSLY WANTS TO
GIVE THE IMPRESSION

20:27.138 --> 20:28.488
HE'S JOHN JOSEPH'S GHOST.

20:28.531 --> 20:30.577
STEALING HIS BODY
MUST BE PART OF THE PLAN.

20:30.620 --> 20:32.100
GOT IT.

20:32.143 --> 20:33.623
THE MOTHER
MAY NOT KNOW ANYTHING

20:33.667 --> 20:36.452
ABOUT HER SON'S BODY BEING
MISSING, SO TREAD LIGHTLY.

20:36.496 --> 20:38.280
ANYTHING ELSE?
YEAH.

20:38.324 --> 20:40.282
SORRY I'M LATE.

20:40.326 --> 20:43.546
HANSEL AND GRETEL
WOULD HAVE LIVED A LOT LONGER

20:43.590 --> 20:45.592
IF THEY HAD HAD TO FIND
THIS DUMP.

20:45.635 --> 20:47.028
HI.
HI.

20:47.071 --> 20:49.335
OLIVE'S COMING.
SHE KNOWS THE WOMAN.

20:49.378 --> 20:50.379
GREAT.

20:51.728 --> 20:53.817
YOU KNOW, HANSEL AND GRETEL
LIVED, BY THE WAY.

20:53.861 --> 20:55.689
ONCE THEY TRICKED THE WITCH
INTO THE OVEN,

20:55.732 --> 20:57.908
THEY STOLE HER JEWELS,
WENT HOME WITH THEIR FATHER,

20:57.952 --> 20:59.649
ONLY TO DISCOVER
THAT THEIR STEPMOTHER,

20:59.693 --> 21:02.043
WHO HAD SENT THEM INTO
THE WOODS, HAD DIED OF EVILNESS.

21:02.086 --> 21:03.871
YOU CAN'T DIE OF EVILNESS.

21:03.914 --> 21:05.742
HAPPENS ALL THE TIME.

21:05.786 --> 21:08.267
YOU DO SOMETHING MEAN
OR HURTFUL TO SOMEONE,
LIKE TELL A SECRET --

21:08.310 --> 21:10.094
BANG! YOU ARE DEAD.

21:10.138 --> 21:11.792
OR BANG!
YOU'RE NOT REALLY DEAD.

21:11.835 --> 21:13.533
YOU'RE JUST PRETENDING
TO BE DEAD,

21:13.576 --> 21:16.318
WHILE OTHER PEOPLE WHO THINK
YOU'RE DEAD ARE HEARTBROKEN.

21:16.362 --> 21:18.277
OR, BANG, YOU TALK TOO MUCH,
AND YOU BOTH GO WAIT IN THE CAR.

21:20.017 --> 21:21.671
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

21:23.282 --> 21:25.458
OH. HELLO.

21:25.501 --> 21:27.155
[ GASPS ] OLIVE!

21:27.198 --> 21:29.157
I NEVER THOUGHT
I'D SEE YOU AGAIN.

21:29.200 --> 21:32.813
WELL, YOU'RE A MODEST DRESSER,
AS ALWAYS.

21:32.856 --> 21:34.510
[ LAUGHS ]

21:36.599 --> 21:39.167
I DO HOPE YOU'LL FORGIVE
ALL THE MESS,

21:39.210 --> 21:40.560
BUT THE HALL OF FAME

21:40.603 --> 21:43.171
IS REMODELING
THEIR EXHIBIT ON JOHNNY.

21:43.214 --> 21:46.087
AND THEY ASKED ME TO GO OVER
ALL OF HIS TROPHIES.

21:46.130 --> 21:47.523
CONGRATULATIONS,
MRS. JACOBS.

21:47.567 --> 21:48.655
THANK YOU.

21:48.698 --> 21:50.134
IT'S PROBABLY JUST AS WELL

21:50.178 --> 21:51.832
THAT YOU TRAMPLED HIM
WHEN YOU DID, OLIVE,

21:51.875 --> 21:54.356
OR ELSE I WOULD HAVE
HAD TO BUY ANOTHER HOUSE

21:54.400 --> 21:56.010
JUST TO PUT
ALL THE TROPHIES IN.

21:56.053 --> 21:57.316
[ LAUGHS ]

21:57.359 --> 21:59.840
I KNOW THAT MUST SOUND
A LITTLE --

21:59.883 --> 22:00.971
BITCHY.

22:01.015 --> 22:03.365
WHAT DID YOU SAY
YOUR NAME WAS?

22:03.409 --> 22:05.933
BRANDON? BUTCH?

22:05.976 --> 22:07.369
CHUCK.
CHUCK.

22:07.413 --> 22:10.503
OH, I KNEW IT WAS SOMETHING
UNLADYLIKE.

22:10.546 --> 22:12.679
[ LAUGHS ]

22:12.722 --> 22:16.291
MY POINT WAS THAT I HAVE
MADE PEACE WITH JOHNNY'S DEATH.

22:16.335 --> 22:17.727
IT WASN'T EASY AT FIRST,

22:17.771 --> 22:20.034
BUT KNOWING
THAT IT WAS AN ACCIDENT,

22:20.077 --> 22:21.862
AND THAT YOU'VE STAYED SINGLE

22:21.905 --> 22:25.082
AND THAT ALL THE REST OF THEM
ARE DRUNKS,

22:25.126 --> 22:27.041
IT MADE IT A LITTLE EASIER.

22:27.084 --> 22:29.304
HOW DO YOU KNOW
I'M STILL SINGLE?

22:29.348 --> 22:31.698
WELL, YOU WOULDN'T NEED
ALL THAT BAIT

22:31.741 --> 22:34.265
IF YOUR BELLY
WERE FULL OF FISH, DEAR.

22:41.098 --> 22:43.971
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
THAT'S A BIG TROPHY.

22:44.014 --> 22:47.453
YES, THAT ONE BELONGS TO ME.

22:47.496 --> 22:50.412
THIS IS JOHNNY'S
FINAL RESTING PLACE.

22:50.456 --> 22:51.457
HIS ASHES.

22:51.500 --> 22:52.762
HIS ASHES?

22:52.806 --> 22:54.242
THEN WHAT DID YOU BURY
AT HIS FUNERAL?

22:54.285 --> 22:55.722
ALL THE GOLD.

22:55.765 --> 22:57.941
HIS HORSE.

22:57.985 --> 22:59.682
YOU SEE, JOHNNY ALWAYS WANTED

22:59.726 --> 23:02.816
TO GIVE THE HORSE THAT MADE
HIS CAREER A HERO'S BURIAL,

23:02.859 --> 23:06.167
BUT THE HEALTH DEPARTMENT
WASN'T TOO KEEN ON THAT,

23:06.210 --> 23:08.735
SO I DID IT IN SECRET.

23:08.778 --> 23:11.085
I WANT YOU TO KNOW,
MRS. JACOBS,

23:11.128 --> 23:12.956
I NEVER SPENT THE WINNINGS
FROM THAT RACE,

23:13.000 --> 23:16.438
UNTIL NOW, TO HIRE MR. COD
TO HELP SOLVE THIS AWFUL MURDER.

23:16.482 --> 23:17.787
OH.

23:17.831 --> 23:22.183
I DO FORGIVE YOU,
OLIVE SNOOK.

23:22.226 --> 23:23.619
THE FALL WAS AN ACCIDENT.

23:23.663 --> 23:25.969
I CAN'T BLAME YOU
FOR NOT SLOWING DOWN.

23:26.013 --> 23:28.015
JOHNNY NEVER DID.

23:33.020 --> 23:35.544
WELL, I GUESS THAT EXPLAINS
THE HORSE SKELETON.

23:35.588 --> 23:37.459
BUT NOT THE MURDER.OR THE GHOST.

23:37.503 --> 23:39.113
I THINK JOHN JOSEPH'S
COME BACK,

23:39.156 --> 23:41.724
AND HE'S COMING AFTER EVERY ONE
OF US WHO WAS IN THAT RACE.

23:41.768 --> 23:42.899
AND I THINK SHE KNOWS IT.

23:42.943 --> 23:45.119
BUT YOU DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

23:45.162 --> 23:47.469
AND SHE FORGAVE YOU.

23:47.513 --> 23:49.515
Narrator: AS THE LITTLE VOICE
IN OLIVE'S HEAD

23:49.558 --> 23:51.691
TOLD HER SOMETHING BAD
WAS ABOUT TO HAPPEN...

23:51.734 --> 23:53.170
WE NEED TO CHECK ON PINKY.

23:53.214 --> 23:55.477
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]WE'RE CLOSED!

23:55.521 --> 23:59.002
Narrator:
...THE NOT-SO-LITTLE VOICE
IN PINKY McCOY'S HEAD AGREED.

23:59.046 --> 24:00.003
[ GASPS ]

24:00.047 --> 24:01.352
[ NEIGHING ]

24:01.396 --> 24:02.571
AAH!

24:07.837 --> 24:09.230
Narrator:
UNAWARE THAT HIS FRIENDS
WERE CLOSING IN ON THE TRAIL

24:09.273 --> 24:10.753
OF WHAT APPEARED TO BE
A MURDEROUS GHOST,

24:10.797 --> 24:14.191
THE PIE MAKER CONTINUED
TO HAUNT HIS OWN PAST.

24:14.235 --> 24:16.498
HALLOWEEN'S
A BUSY TIME FOR US.

24:16.542 --> 24:18.935
SOME OF
THE NEIGHBORHOOD CHILDREN

24:18.979 --> 24:21.329
STARTED A RUMOR
WE WERE WITCHES.

24:21.372 --> 24:24.375
THEY SAID WE TURNED
LITTLE BOYS INTO BIRDS.

24:24.419 --> 24:27.030
THAT'S...TERRIBLE.

24:27.074 --> 24:28.510
[ BIRD CAWS ]

24:28.554 --> 24:30.817
HELP ME. HELP ME.
THEY TURNED ME INTO A BIRD.

24:30.860 --> 24:34.516
SCARES THE WILLIES
OUT OF THEM.

24:34.560 --> 24:37.345
LILY, VIVIAN,

24:37.388 --> 24:40.696
DO YOU REMEMBER VERY MUCH
ABOUT MY FATHER?

24:40.740 --> 24:41.871
UH...

24:43.090 --> 24:44.657
UH, NO.

24:44.700 --> 24:49.183
A NEIGHBOR'S A NEIGHBOR.
HARD TO REMEMBER SO LONG AGO.

24:49.226 --> 24:51.098
HE WAS A HANDSOME MAN.

24:51.141 --> 24:54.841
AND HE LIKED TO EDGE HIS LAWN
ON SATURDAYS.

24:54.884 --> 24:57.539
[ EXHALES DEEPLY ]
YOUR FATHER WAS A JACKASS.

24:57.583 --> 25:00.150
EVERYBODY SAID
HOW TERRIBLE IT WAS

25:00.194 --> 25:02.370
WHEN HE MOVED AWAY
LIKE THAT.

25:02.413 --> 25:04.938
YOU ASK ME,
HE DID US ALL A FAVOR,

25:04.981 --> 25:07.070
YOU INCLUDED.

25:14.730 --> 25:15.905
[ GAGS ]

25:17.603 --> 25:20.562
Narrator: THE PIE MAKER STARED
AT THE RIPE STRAWBERRY

25:20.606 --> 25:23.217
THAT HAD TURNED ROTTEN
AT THE TOUCH OF HIS TONGUE.

25:23.260 --> 25:24.697
IT COULD ONLY MEAN ONE THING.

25:24.740 --> 25:26.960
HE HAD TOUCHED IT BEFORE.

25:27.003 --> 25:28.614
WHERE DID YOU GET THIS PIE?

25:28.657 --> 25:31.094
WE THOUGHT YOU WERE
HAVING THEM DELIVERED.

25:31.138 --> 25:32.443
COMES EVERY WEEK.

25:32.487 --> 25:35.055
I DON'T KNOW HOW WE SURVIVED
WITHOUT IT.

25:35.098 --> 25:36.752
IT'S LIKE A SEX ADDICTION.

25:38.319 --> 25:40.451
I WOULD IMAGINE.

25:42.192 --> 25:43.933
Narrator:
THE PIE MAKER REALIZED

25:43.977 --> 25:45.892
LILY AND VIVIAN
HAD THEIR OWN GHOST.

25:45.935 --> 25:49.983
OH, IF THIS
IS THAT ARMENIAN BAKER

25:50.026 --> 25:52.420
PULLING SOME KIND OF
SWITCHEROO --

25:52.463 --> 25:54.770
NO. NO.

25:54.814 --> 25:56.424
IT'S ME.

25:56.467 --> 25:58.861
I'M SENDING THEM.

25:58.905 --> 26:01.385
I JUST FIGURED YOU COULD USE
A LITTLE SWEETNESS

26:01.429 --> 26:02.735
IN THESE HARD TIMES.

26:04.780 --> 26:06.086
I, UH...

26:06.129 --> 26:08.131
I REALLY GOT TO GO.

26:09.698 --> 26:11.613
NED, WAIT.

26:11.657 --> 26:13.789
NED.

26:13.833 --> 26:15.486
YOUR FATHER --
I KNOW.

26:15.530 --> 26:17.750
HE WAS EMOTIONALLY STUNTED,
AFRAID OF GETTING CLOSE.

26:17.793 --> 26:19.447
DEFINITELY NOT THE BEST
AT GOODBYES.

26:19.490 --> 26:21.928
"JACKASS" IS AS GOOD
A WORD AS ANY.

26:21.971 --> 26:24.757
THEN WHY DO I STILL
MISS HIM?

26:24.800 --> 26:28.717
WE SEE
WHAT WE WANT TO SEE.

26:28.761 --> 26:33.766
SOMETIMES I PUT PILLOWS UNDER
THE COVERS OF CHARLOTTE'S BED

26:33.809 --> 26:36.116
AND PRETEND SHE'S SLEEPING.

26:36.159 --> 26:39.336
I MISS HER, TOO.

26:40.686 --> 26:42.949
NOBODY REMEMBERS
YOUR FATHER, NED.

26:42.992 --> 26:44.733
WHAT THEY DO TALK ABOUT

26:44.777 --> 26:48.911
IS HOW YOU TURNED OUT TO BE
SUCH A NICE, WONDERFUL BOY.

26:51.740 --> 26:53.655
MAN, EVEN.

27:05.711 --> 27:07.277
I'LL KEEP THE PIES COMING.

27:08.844 --> 27:10.890
Narrator: AS THE PIE MAKER
STARTED OFF,

27:10.933 --> 27:13.501
HE REALIZED THAT,
FOR THE FIRST TIME IN HIS LIFE,

27:13.544 --> 27:16.722
HE MISSED SOMETHING
MORE THAN HIS PAST.

27:16.765 --> 27:18.637
HE MISSED HIS PRESENT.

27:20.290 --> 27:22.423
WHERE HAVE YOU BEEN?

27:22.466 --> 27:23.685
NOT IMPORTANT.

27:23.729 --> 27:26.383
IT'S IMPORTANT TO ME.
I MISSED YOU.

27:28.037 --> 27:30.518
[ High-pitched voice ]
I MISSED YOU, TOO.

27:30.561 --> 27:33.826
[ Normal voice ] CAN WE
GET ON WITH THIS, PLEASE?

27:34.870 --> 27:35.958
OLIVE.

27:38.439 --> 27:40.136
COME ON.
LET'S GO OUTSIDE.

27:40.180 --> 27:42.748
WE'LL LET EMERSON AND NED
LOOK FOR EVIDENCE.

27:42.791 --> 27:44.010
COME ON.

27:52.583 --> 27:56.152
[ WATCH TICKING ]

27:56.196 --> 27:58.807
AW, CRAP.

27:58.851 --> 28:00.243
I NEED A DRINK.

28:07.250 --> 28:08.469
ALL RIGHT,
WHO DID THIS?

28:08.512 --> 28:09.862
WOULDN'T HAVE BELIEVED

28:09.905 --> 28:12.473
IF I HADN'T SEEN IT
WITH MY OWN EYES --

28:12.516 --> 28:17.086
SAME SILKS, SAME GOGGLES,
SAME AS THE DAY HE DIED.

28:17.130 --> 28:19.132
THE GHOST DID IT.

28:19.175 --> 28:20.524
FINALLY GOT HIS REVENGE.

28:20.568 --> 28:22.048
NOT THAT I DON'T DESERVE IT,

28:22.091 --> 28:24.224
AS I'M THE ONE
WHO GAVE HIM THE SNIP.

28:24.267 --> 28:25.486
WHAT SNIP?

28:25.529 --> 28:26.879
LET'S JUST SAY

28:26.922 --> 28:29.620
I PLAYED THE PONIES
BETTER THAN I RODE THEM.

28:29.664 --> 28:31.492
YOU BET ON YOUR OWN RACES.

28:31.535 --> 28:33.059
ONLY THE ONES I FIXED.

28:33.102 --> 28:35.888
YOU SEE OLIVE,
YOU TELL HER I'M SORRY.

28:35.931 --> 28:38.455
SHE DON'T DESERVE
WHAT'S COMING TO HER.

28:38.499 --> 28:40.109
WHAT'S SHE GOT
COMING TO HER?

28:40.153 --> 28:42.416
IT'S PRETTY CLEAR
JOHN JOSEPH'S COME BACK

28:42.459 --> 28:44.592
BECAUSE HE KNOWS
HOW WE ALL KEPT THE SECRET.

28:44.635 --> 28:45.636
WHAT SECRET?

28:45.680 --> 28:47.551
MAKE YOURSELF COMFORTABLE.

28:47.595 --> 28:49.379
IT'S QUITE A STORY.

28:54.297 --> 28:56.299
SON OF A BITCH.

29:00.826 --> 29:02.523
OLIVE!OLIVE!

29:02.566 --> 29:05.395
Narrator: AS OLIVE
WAS CONFRONTED WITH THE LIE

29:05.439 --> 29:08.529
THAT PINKY HAD BRIEFLY REVIVED
TO POINT THE FINGER,

29:08.572 --> 29:11.097
SHE BROKE DOWN.

29:11.140 --> 29:12.751
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

29:12.794 --> 29:14.187
IN THE PANDEMONIUM

29:14.230 --> 29:17.494
THAT FOLLOWED THE TRAGEDY-MARRED
JOCK-OFF 2000,

29:17.538 --> 29:21.629
THE FOUR SURVIVING JOCKEYS,
PINKY, LUCAS, GORDON, AND OLIVE,

29:21.672 --> 29:23.413
GATHERED IN SECRET.

29:23.457 --> 29:27.156
ONE OF THEM HAD DELIBERATELY
CUT THE FALLEN JOCKEY'S GIRTH.

29:27.200 --> 29:31.291
JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS
HAD BEEN SABOTAGED.

29:31.334 --> 29:32.466
ACCUSATIONS FLEW.

29:32.509 --> 29:33.946
BUT TO PROTECT THEIR OWN HONOR,

29:33.989 --> 29:36.513
AND THAT
OF THEIR STORIED PROFESSION,

29:36.557 --> 29:39.778
THE HEINOUS CRIME WOULD NEVER
BE REVEALED TO ANYONE.

29:39.821 --> 29:41.257
OLIVE TRIED TO PROTEST...

29:41.301 --> 29:42.563
NO.

29:42.606 --> 29:43.999
Narrator:
...BUT SHE WAS OVERWHELMED.

29:44.043 --> 29:47.133
THE OATH TO KEEP
THE TERRIBLE SECRET WAS TAKEN

29:47.176 --> 29:49.918
AND THE EVIDENCE DESTROYED.

29:56.795 --> 29:59.145
YOU'RE IN A LOT OF DANGER.

29:59.188 --> 30:01.234
I'M SORRY I DIDN'T TELL YOU
ABOUT THE GIRTH.

30:01.277 --> 30:03.671
WHY WOULD YOU SPEND ALL THOSE
YEARS LYING FOR EACH OTHER?

30:03.714 --> 30:05.281
WE TOOK AN OATH.

30:05.325 --> 30:07.370
I WAS SCARED FOR WHAT
WOULD HAPPEN IF I BROKE IT.

30:07.414 --> 30:08.850
SOMETIMES YOU HAVE TO
KEEP A SECRET,

30:08.894 --> 30:10.156
EVEN IF IT MEANS
HURTING SOMEONE.

30:10.199 --> 30:11.548
EXACTLY.

30:12.636 --> 30:14.247
DAMN IT.

30:14.290 --> 30:16.423
Emerson: BOTTOM LINE IS,
SOMEONE WANTS TO GET PAYBACK

30:16.466 --> 30:18.381
EITHER 'CAUSE THEY FOUND OUT
ABOUT THE SECRET,

30:18.425 --> 30:20.079
OR BECAUSE THEY KNEW ABOUT IT
ALL ALONG

30:20.122 --> 30:21.341
AND WANT IT TO GO AWAY FOREVER.

30:21.384 --> 30:23.038
THAT ONLY LEAVES
GORDON AND YOU.

30:23.082 --> 30:25.780
I DIDN'T DO IT,
AND IT CERTAINLY WASN'T GORDON.

30:25.824 --> 30:27.347
WE GOT TO FIND GORDON
BEFORE SOMEBODY ELSE DOES.

30:27.390 --> 30:29.349
BUT IF IT IS A GHOST...

30:29.392 --> 30:31.438
I'M GETTING THE CAR.

30:31.481 --> 30:33.570
ALL I'M SAYING,

30:33.614 --> 30:34.963
IF THIS IS SOME SPIRIT

30:35.007 --> 30:36.573
TRYING TO CORRECT
A TERRIBLE WRONG,

30:36.617 --> 30:39.054
THEN YOU NEED TO CONFRONT IT
AND TELL IT TO MOVE ON.

30:39.098 --> 30:40.534
IF I WERE A GHOST,

30:40.577 --> 30:43.624
IT WOULD BE HARD FOR ME
TO MOVE ON, TOO.

30:45.060 --> 30:47.193
I'M SURE IT WOULD BE.

30:50.587 --> 30:52.807
KEEP THE CURTAINS CLOSED
AND THE WINDOWS LOCKED

30:52.851 --> 30:54.026
FOR THE REST OF THE NIGHT.

30:54.069 --> 30:56.158
YES, SIR.

30:57.725 --> 30:58.769
HEY.

31:00.293 --> 31:01.816
BE CAREFUL.

31:01.860 --> 31:04.253
I WILL. YOU TOO.

31:06.995 --> 31:09.911
LOCK THE DOOR BEHIND ME
AND DON'T LET ANYONE IN.

31:09.955 --> 31:11.521
MM-HMM.

31:14.611 --> 31:15.917
I LOVE IN-CHARGE NED.

31:15.961 --> 31:17.919
YOU REALLY
DON'T HAVE TO STAY.

31:17.963 --> 31:20.095
I CAN TOTALLY
TAKE CARE OF MYSELF.

31:20.139 --> 31:21.575
YOU'RE NOT SCARED?

31:21.618 --> 31:22.793
NO.

31:22.837 --> 31:24.447
WHY? ARE YOU?

31:24.491 --> 31:25.927
NO.

31:27.494 --> 31:29.757
I'LL MAKE SOME TEA.

31:29.800 --> 31:31.498
AND I'LL GET THE BOOZE
TO TAKE THE EDGE OFF.

31:31.541 --> 31:33.630
BOURBON,
WITH A SPLASH OF CHAMOMILE.

31:33.674 --> 31:35.676
AUNT LILY'S FAVORITE.

31:35.719 --> 31:38.070
HEY, OLIVE...

31:38.113 --> 31:40.115
THANK YOU
FOR RESPECTING MY SECRET.

31:40.159 --> 31:42.944
I'D NEVER DO THIS TO MY AUNTS
IF I DIDN'T HAVE TO.

31:42.988 --> 31:45.947
I WON'T TELL NED.
I'LL LEAVE THAT UP TO YOU.

31:47.296 --> 31:49.646
I KEEP THE BOOZE
BY MY BED.

31:59.700 --> 32:02.398
JOHN JOSEPH.

32:02.442 --> 32:04.748
IF YOU'RE...

32:04.792 --> 32:06.837
SCARED OF A GHOST,
CONFRONT IT.

32:09.144 --> 32:12.539
HEY, OLIVE,
I LOVE YOUR HORSEY MUGS.

32:12.582 --> 32:15.150
[ WIND BLOWS ]

32:15.194 --> 32:16.804
OLIVE?

32:16.847 --> 32:19.328
OLIVE?!

32:20.329 --> 32:21.940
OLIVE?!

32:35.605 --> 32:38.086
AAAH!

32:39.522 --> 32:41.568
IT IS YOU!

32:46.094 --> 32:47.922
JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS.

32:47.966 --> 32:49.271
IT'S REALLY YOU?

32:54.450 --> 32:56.148
OH, NICE SHOT.
ARE YOU OKAY?

32:56.191 --> 32:58.019
I FOUND THIS
OUTSIDE THE WINDOW.

32:58.063 --> 33:00.021
I GAVE THIS
TO JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS

33:00.065 --> 33:02.719
RIGHT BEFORE
THE JOCK-OFF 2000
FOR GOOD LUCK.

33:02.763 --> 33:05.374
OLIVE?

33:05.418 --> 33:07.681
JOHN JOSEPH,
I THOUGHT YOU WERE DEAD.

33:07.724 --> 33:09.683
YOU SHOULD BE ASHAMED
OF YOURSELF...

33:13.295 --> 33:15.950
...AND ABOUT
TWO FEET SHORTER.

33:15.994 --> 33:19.040
LET ME EXPLAIN.

33:19.084 --> 33:20.781
Narrator:
THE FACTS WERE THESE --

33:20.824 --> 33:23.914
JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS
HAD INDEED DIED ON THE TRACK

33:23.958 --> 33:25.133
THAT FATEFUL DAY.

33:25.177 --> 33:26.439
CLEAR![ ELECTRICAL CHARGE ]

33:26.482 --> 33:28.267
Narrator:
BUT THE SHOCK OF 1,200 VOLTS

33:28.310 --> 33:31.270
BROUGHT HIS HEART BACK TO LIFE.

33:31.313 --> 33:34.925
UNFORTUNATELY,
HIS LEGS WOULD NOT BE SO LUCKY.

33:34.969 --> 33:37.058
CONSULTING WITH THE FAMILY,

33:37.102 --> 33:41.628
THE DOCTORS TURNED TO ANOTHER
RACER WHO HAD FALLEN THAT DAY.

33:41.671 --> 33:44.065
AFTER A 14-HOUR SURGERY,

33:44.109 --> 33:46.720
ALL THE GOLD WOULD LIVE ON...

33:46.763 --> 33:50.550
BELOW THE BELT
OF JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS.

33:50.593 --> 33:51.899
WE THOUGHT
YOU WERE A GHOST.

33:51.942 --> 33:53.379
[ BOTH LAUGHING ]

33:53.422 --> 33:56.512
WELL, I'VE BASICALLY BEEN
LIVING IN MAMA'S BASEMENT

33:56.556 --> 33:58.079
FOR THE PAST SEVEN YEARS.

33:58.123 --> 34:00.560
WHEN I HEARD YOU TALKING
ABOUT SHOEMAKER

34:00.603 --> 34:02.083
THROUGH THE HEATING VENT,

34:02.127 --> 34:03.650
I THOUGHT I WAS DREAMING.

34:03.693 --> 34:06.087
DID YOU KILL HIM,
JOHN JOSEPH JACOBS?

34:06.131 --> 34:07.871
OF COURSE NOT.

34:07.915 --> 34:10.265
WHY WOULD I WANT TO KILL ANYBODY
IF IT WAS JUST AN ACCIDENT?

34:13.399 --> 34:15.357
THEN WHO WOULD BE
TRYING TO FRAME YOU?

34:15.401 --> 34:16.576
I DON'T KNOW.

34:16.619 --> 34:18.230
TRUTH IS,
I'VE DONE MY BEST

34:18.273 --> 34:20.493
TO FORGET THAT WHOLE CHAPTER
OF MY LIFE.

34:20.536 --> 34:24.236
I GUESS I KIND OF
TRIED THAT, TOO.

34:24.279 --> 34:26.107
CAN WE GO BACK A LITTLE?

34:26.151 --> 34:29.110
YOU HAVE, UM,
HORSE LEGS?

34:29.154 --> 34:32.287
IT'S CALLED XENOGRAFT
BONE TRANSPLANTATION.

34:32.331 --> 34:34.289
THOSE DOCTORS WERE ARTISTS.

34:34.333 --> 34:35.986
IT ONLY TOOK TWO YEARS

34:36.030 --> 34:38.685
UNTIL I COULD WALK UP
THE BASEMENT STAIRS ON MY OWN,

34:38.728 --> 34:42.123
AND ONLY ANOTHER THREE
UNTIL MY MAMA LET ME.

34:42.167 --> 34:44.125
I'M SO SORRY YOUR MOM
KEEPS YOU IN THE BASEMENT.

34:44.169 --> 34:46.127
NO, IT'S MY CHOICE NOW.

34:46.171 --> 34:48.173
I FEEL SAFE DOWN THERE.

34:48.216 --> 34:50.784
BESIDES, SINCE THE OPERATION,

34:50.827 --> 34:54.135
MAMA THOUGHT
I MIGHT SCARE PEOPLE.

34:54.179 --> 34:57.269
IS THAT WHY YOU'VE BEEN
HIDING IN THE BASEMENT?

34:57.312 --> 34:59.314
JOHN JOSEPH,
YOU LOOK GREAT.

34:59.358 --> 35:02.143
AND YOU BEAT DEATH.
YOU'RE ALIVE.

35:02.187 --> 35:03.231
YAY!YAY!

35:03.275 --> 35:05.015
DON'T YOU OWE IT
TO YOUR HORSE

35:05.059 --> 35:08.323
TO STAND UP ON HIS TWO LEGS
AND GET OUT THERE AND LIVE?

35:08.367 --> 35:11.152
MAYBE YOU'RE RIGHT.

35:11.196 --> 35:13.154
MAYBE IT'S TIME
TO TELL MY MOTHER

35:13.198 --> 35:16.984
I'M READY
TO GET OUT THERE ON MY OWN.

35:17.027 --> 35:19.639
I MEAN, GEEZ,
I'M ALMOST 40.

35:19.682 --> 35:23.295
JOHN JOSEPH, DO YOU WANT US
TO HELP YOU TALK TO HER?

35:23.338 --> 35:25.471
THAT WOULD BE GREAT.

35:25.514 --> 35:28.604
OH, AND I KIND OF
NEED A RIDE HOME.

35:35.524 --> 35:38.658
MY MAMA'S STILL
AT HER AQUA THERAPY.

35:38.701 --> 35:40.529
MAKE YOURSELF AT HOME.

35:40.573 --> 35:41.661
OH. THANKS!

35:45.317 --> 35:46.361
Hey. Hey.

35:46.405 --> 35:47.536
What?

35:47.580 --> 35:48.885
If John Joseph
didn't do it,

35:48.929 --> 35:50.496
then the killer's
still out there.

35:50.539 --> 35:52.628
John Joseph: SWIZZLE STICKS!
WE'RE OUT OF CRACKERS.

35:55.196 --> 35:56.458
CRACKERS?

35:56.502 --> 35:59.200
OYSTER CRACKERS.
I HAVE LOW BLOOD SUGAR.

35:59.244 --> 36:03.248
I KIND OF GET CRAZY-GRUMPY
IF I DON'T WATCH IT.

36:03.291 --> 36:05.641
I HAVE MORE BAGS DOWNSTAIRS.

36:07.252 --> 36:08.253
THIS TROPHY BUGS ME.

36:08.296 --> 36:09.689
Olive, there --

36:09.732 --> 36:12.039
there were oyster crackers
at every murder scene.

36:12.082 --> 36:13.867
If he's alive,

36:13.910 --> 36:16.870
then what do you think
she keeps in here?

36:16.913 --> 36:19.264
I don't know, but hurry up and
open it before he comes back.

36:19.307 --> 36:22.354
What if he changes when
his blood-sugar level drops?

36:22.397 --> 36:24.138
Like a hypoglycemic
werewolf?

36:24.182 --> 36:25.661
Hurry up!

36:27.620 --> 36:28.882
EW.

36:28.925 --> 36:31.232
THERE AREASHES IN HERE.

36:31.276 --> 36:34.104
WHAT IF HE'S
GONNA GO GET HIS HORSE?

36:34.148 --> 36:36.759
[ HORSE NEIGHS ]

36:36.803 --> 36:37.891
OLIVE![ GASPING ]

36:37.934 --> 36:40.633
LOOK!

36:40.676 --> 36:43.113
IT'S JOHN JOSEPH JACOB'S
SADDLE.

36:43.157 --> 36:45.159
HE DOES KNOW THE SECRET.
YES.

36:46.813 --> 36:48.031
[ NEIGHING ]

37:03.743 --> 37:05.484
Narrator:
AS OLIVE PREPARED TO BE
THE GHOST RIDER'S THIRD VICTIM,

37:05.527 --> 37:08.748
GORDON CONSIDERED THE SOBER
PROSPECT OF BEING THE FOURTH.

37:08.791 --> 37:13.927
[ Slurring ]
♪ AND NEVER BROUGHT TO MIND

37:13.970 --> 37:15.581
CAN YOU NOT SING?

37:15.624 --> 37:18.105
IF I DON'T SING,
I THROW UP.

37:18.148 --> 37:19.367
SING.

37:21.543 --> 37:24.285
I MISS PINKY.

37:24.329 --> 37:27.245
I EVEN MISS SHOEY.

37:27.288 --> 37:29.203
THEY WERE GOOD PEOPLE.

37:29.247 --> 37:34.861
EVEN AFTER SHOEY GOT ON THE
WAGON AND BECAME AN EPIC BORE,

37:34.904 --> 37:36.645
I LOVED HIM.

37:36.689 --> 37:38.430
HE STOPPED DRINKING?

37:38.473 --> 37:40.040
THAT POOR SUCKER.

37:40.083 --> 37:43.304
HE EVEN MADE AMENDS
TO JOHN JOSEPH'S MOTHER

37:43.348 --> 37:44.523
BEFORE HE DIED.

37:44.566 --> 37:47.090
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
"MADE AMENDS"?

37:47.134 --> 37:49.745
TOLD THE OLD BAG OF NAILS
EVERYTHING.

37:49.789 --> 37:53.923
HE EVEN BROUGHT HER THE ASHES
FROM THE SADDLE TO PROVE IT.

37:54.924 --> 37:56.709
GO.

37:56.752 --> 37:58.406
[ NEIGHING ]

38:01.583 --> 38:04.804
MAMA JACOBS,
YOU KILLED LUCAS AND PINKY?

38:04.847 --> 38:08.547
AS FAR AS ANYONE KNOWS,
IT WAS THE GHOST OF JOHN JOSEPH,

38:08.590 --> 38:10.549
AND IT'S GONNA STAY THAT WAY.

38:10.592 --> 38:13.160
THE CRACKERS
WERE A NICE TOUCH.

38:13.203 --> 38:15.423
HYPOGLYCEMIA
IS HEREDITARY, SWEETIE.

38:15.467 --> 38:18.774
I TRAMPLED THEM JUST THE WAY
THEY DID MY BOY.

38:18.818 --> 38:20.733
BUT JOHN JOSEPH IS ALIVE.

38:20.776 --> 38:22.256
THEY MURDERED HIS CAREER.

38:22.300 --> 38:24.258
HE COULD'VE WON
THE TRIPLE CROWN.

38:24.302 --> 38:26.652
HE COULD'VE BEEN
THE BEST THERE EVER WAS.

38:26.695 --> 38:29.611
OLIVE IS INNOCENT.
SHE DIDN'T CUT THE GIRTH.

38:29.655 --> 38:32.092
BUT I KEPT THE SECRET.
SHH!

38:32.135 --> 38:34.660
NOW THAT WE'VE REESTABLISHED
WHY I NEED TO KILL YOU,

38:34.703 --> 38:36.444
IT'S TIME FOR YOU TO RUN.

38:36.488 --> 38:40.666
I HAVE FOUND THAT TRAMPLING
WORKS BETTER AT A FULL GALLOP.

38:40.709 --> 38:42.102
COME ON!

38:42.145 --> 38:44.278
[ NEIGHING ]

38:48.456 --> 38:49.805
Olive: HURRY!

38:49.849 --> 38:52.025
BE CAREFUL. BE CAREFUL.
COME ON. COME ON.

38:52.068 --> 38:55.333
[ NEIGHING ]

38:57.335 --> 38:58.336
THEY'RE NOT THERE.

38:58.379 --> 39:00.250
[ NEIGHING IN DISTANCE ]

39:00.294 --> 39:01.600
THE WOODS!

39:03.993 --> 39:06.692
[ EXHALES CONTENTLY ]

39:06.735 --> 39:09.608
COME ON.

39:10.565 --> 39:11.784
[ NEIGHING ]

39:11.827 --> 39:13.873
WATCH OUT.

39:13.916 --> 39:15.309
AH!

39:15.353 --> 39:16.441
AAH!

39:16.484 --> 39:17.659
OH, MY ANKLE.

39:17.703 --> 39:19.792
HERE! HERE, PUT YOUR ARM
AROUND ME.

39:19.835 --> 39:21.402
YOU GOT IT.
YOU GOT IT.

39:21.446 --> 39:24.013
LEAN ON ME.

39:26.668 --> 39:28.453
HURRY! HURRY!

39:28.496 --> 39:29.454
OW!

39:29.497 --> 39:30.846
OH! ARE YOU OKAY?

39:32.195 --> 39:33.153
AH!

39:33.196 --> 39:34.720
ARE YOU OKAY?

39:34.763 --> 39:35.895
RUN. SAVE YOURSELF.

39:35.938 --> 39:37.549
NO. NO.
SHE'S AFTER ME, NOT YOU.

39:37.592 --> 39:38.811
TELL NED I LOVE...

39:40.247 --> 39:41.988
...HIS PIES.

39:42.031 --> 39:43.990
BUT -- OLIVE!

39:44.033 --> 39:44.991
OLIVE!

39:45.034 --> 39:46.775
OVER HERE!

39:46.819 --> 39:48.821
♪ THE OLD GRAY MARE,
SHE AIN'T WHAT SHE USED TO BE ♪

39:48.864 --> 39:51.389
♪ AIN'T WHAT SHE USED TO BE,
AIN'T WHAT SHE USED TO BE ♪

39:51.432 --> 39:52.433
♪ AIN'T WHAT SHE USED TO BE

39:52.477 --> 39:54.043
AAAH!

39:54.087 --> 39:55.567
Ned: OLIVE!
NED?

39:58.091 --> 39:59.527
[ CLANG! ]

40:01.703 --> 40:03.792
[ LAUGHS ]

40:03.836 --> 40:05.228
I LOVE YOU, SHOVEL.

40:05.272 --> 40:07.448
ARE YOU OKAY?

40:07.492 --> 40:09.668
YOU SAVED ME.

40:09.711 --> 40:11.060
HEY, DI--

40:12.888 --> 40:14.368
OLIVE! OLIVE!

40:14.412 --> 40:15.413
Chuck: NED?

40:18.416 --> 40:20.156
CHUCK?

40:24.247 --> 40:27.468
Narrator:
THOUGH OLIVE SNOOK HAD WON
THE RACE FOR HER LIFE,

40:27.512 --> 40:29.557
IN THE RACE
FOR THE PIE MAKER'S HEART,

40:29.601 --> 40:32.908
SHE HAD, ONCE AGAIN,
PLACED SECOND.

40:32.952 --> 40:36.042
AS FOR MAMA JACOBS,
THIS RACE WOULD BE HER LAST.

40:36.085 --> 40:38.697
SHE HAD ALWAYS SEEN HER SON
AS A WINNER

40:38.740 --> 40:40.873
AND COULD NOT SEE HIM
AS ANYTHING ELSE.

40:40.916 --> 40:42.483
HER MURDEROUS GRIP ON THE PAST

40:42.527 --> 40:46.966
LANDED HER A TRIP
TO A PRIVATE MUSEUM FOR ONE.

40:47.009 --> 40:50.709
OLIVE OFFERED JOHN JOSEPH THE
TROPHY FROM THE JOCK-OFF 2000

40:50.752 --> 40:52.885
SHE FELT WAS RIGHTFULLY HIS.

40:52.928 --> 40:54.626
OH, I COULDN'T POSSIBLY.

40:54.669 --> 40:56.410
Narrator:
HE TOOK IT...

40:56.454 --> 41:00.632
AS WELL AS THE UNSPENT PURSE,
WHICH HE HAPPILY ACCEPTED.

41:00.675 --> 41:03.243
Chuck: I'M SO GLAD
YOU BROUGHT ME BACK HERE.

41:03.286 --> 41:06.246
Ned: I HAVEN'T BEEN BACK
IN A LONG TIME.

41:06.289 --> 41:09.075
I HAD TO
CONFRONT A GHOST TODAY.

41:09.118 --> 41:11.425
WHOSE GHOST?

41:11.469 --> 41:12.905
MY OWN.

41:15.473 --> 41:17.300
I KNOW ABOUT
THE PIES, CHUCK.

41:17.344 --> 41:18.737
HMM?

41:21.304 --> 41:22.741
DID EMERSON TELL YOU?

41:22.784 --> 41:23.742
NO.

41:23.785 --> 41:24.830
OLIVE?

41:24.873 --> 41:26.179
OLIVE?

41:26.222 --> 41:27.615
I MEAN, YOU'RE NOT MAD?

41:27.659 --> 41:30.096
NO.

41:30.139 --> 41:33.142
I UNDERSTAND.

41:38.060 --> 41:40.585
COME ON, THERE'S SOMETHING
YOU GOT TO DO.

41:42.064 --> 41:43.805
[ High-pitched voice ]
OOOOOOH!

41:53.293 --> 41:54.599
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

41:54.642 --> 41:57.340
Vivian:
IS THAT CLOCK RIGHT?

41:57.384 --> 41:59.212
IT'S 2:00 IN THE A.M.

41:59.255 --> 42:01.475
Lily: [ GROANS ]
I'LL GET MY GUN.

42:01.519 --> 42:04.522
AND I'LL GET
THE CANDY BOWL.

42:06.698 --> 42:08.395
OH.

42:08.438 --> 42:10.266
TRICK OR TREAT.

42:15.663 --> 42:17.665
THANK YOU.

